# WordPress Theme to Static HTML/JS Site Conversion

## Strategy Overview

Extract a WordPress theme into a fully standalone static site with zero server-side dependencies. The result is a folder of HTML, CSS, JS, and images deployable to any web host, CDN, or S3 bucket.

## Step 1: Inventory the WordPress Theme

Map every dynamic element to its static replacement:

| WordPress Feature | Static Replacement |
|---|---|
| Customizer settings (`get_theme_mod`) | Hardcoded text in HTML |
| Customizer icon dropdowns (`select` type) | Hardcoded `<i class="fas fa-icon">` in HTML |
| `lo_get_icon_choices()` helper | Remove entirely — icons are now static class strings |
| Conditional rendering (`if ! empty(trim($text))`) | Include the element if it has content, remove if not |
| CSS `auto-fit` + `minmax` grids | Switch back to fixed columns (`repeat(N, 1fr)`) matching the actual number of items, or keep `auto-fit` for responsive flexibility |
| Custom Post Types (WP_Query loops) | Hardcoded HTML cards/sections |
| CPT meta box icon dropdowns | Hardcoded icon class on each card's `<i>` tag |
| `wp_nav_menu()` + Walker | Static `<ul><li><a>` nav |
| Contact Form 7 shortcode | HTML `<form>` with FormSubmit.co, Formspree, or Netlify Forms |
| `wp_enqueue_style/script` | `<link>` and `<script>` tags in `<head>` / before `</body>` |
| `wp_head()` / `wp_footer()` | Remove entirely (replace with explicit link/script tags) |
| `get_template_directory_uri()` | Relative paths (`./images/`, `./css/`, `./js/`) |
| `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()` etc. | Remove — static HTML needs no runtime escaping |
| `body_class()`, `language_attributes()` | Hardcode: `<html lang="nb">`, `<body>` |
| `get_header()` / `get_footer()` | Inline the header/footer HTML directly |
| `get_template_part()` | Inline each section's HTML into the page |

## Step 2: Extract Content

### From the Customizer

1. Open each `inc/customizer.php` setting and note the `'default'` value — this is the original static text.
2. Alternatively, if the site is live, use the Customizer preview to copy current values.
3. For each `lo_get_option('key', 'default')` call in template parts, replace with the literal default string.
4. For icon dropdown settings, take the `'default'` icon class (e.g. `'fa-user-md'`) and hardcode it into the `<i class="fas fa-user-md">` tag.
5. Remove ALL conditional rendering wrappers (`if ( ! empty( trim( ... ) ) )`) — in a static site, you decide at build time which elements exist.

### From Custom Post Types

1. Open wp-admin and export CPT content (or read `theme-setup.php` seed data).
2. For each CPT loop in a template part, replace with hardcoded HTML cards containing the actual content.
3. For CPTs with icon meta boxes, look up the icon value (`get_post_meta( $id, '_behandling_icon', true )`) from the seed data in `theme-setup.php` and hardcode the appropriate Font Awesome class.
4. If the CPT was seeded with ordering (`menu_order`), preserve that order in the static HTML.

Example — converting a behandlere (staff) WP_Query loop:

```html
<!-- Before: WP_Query loop -->
<!-- After: Static HTML -->
<div class="staff-card">
    <div class="staff-photo">
        <img src="images/thomas.jpg" alt="Thomas Sewell">
    </div>
    <div class="staff-info">
        <h3>Thomas Sewell</h3>
        <p class="staff-title">Osteopat D.O. MNOF & Fysioterapeut</p>
        <p class="staff-bio">Bio text here...</p>
    </div>
</div>
```

### From Contact Form 7

Replace CF7 shortcode with a static HTML form using a third-party service:

```html
<form action="https://formsubmit.co/your@email.com" method="POST">
    <input type="text" name="_honey" style="display:none">
    <input type="hidden" name="_captcha" value="false">
    <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="New enquiry from website">
    <div class="form-group">
        <label>Name <span class="required">*</span></label>
        <input type="text" name="name" required>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        <label>Email <span class="required">*</span></label>
        <input type="email" name="email" required>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
        <label>Message <span class="required">*</span></label>
        <textarea name="message" rows="5" required></textarea>
    </div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Send</button>
</form>
```

Alternatives: Formspree.io, Netlify Forms, Basin, or a custom serverless function.

## Step 3: Build the Static File Structure

```
site-name/
├── index.html           # Single HTML file (or multiple for multi-page)
├── styles.css           # Combined from WP style.css (strip theme header comment)
├── script.js            # From assets/js/script.js
├── images/              # From assets/images/ (flatten the path)
└── deploy.ps1           # Optional deployment script
```

## Step 4: Assemble index.html

Build the HTML file by inlining all template parts in order:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="nb">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Site Title</title>
    <!-- Fonts and icons from wp_enqueue_style calls -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=..." rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/.../font-awesome/...">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- header.php content (nav) -->
    <!-- section-hero.php content -->
    <!-- section-about.php content -->
    <!-- ... all sections in order from front-page.php ... -->
    <!-- footer.php content -->

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Step 5: Clean the CSS

1. Copy the WordPress `style.css` content.
2. **Remove** the theme header comment block (`Theme Name:`, `Text Domain:`, etc.).
3. **Remove** any WordPress-specific CSS (admin bar spacing, CF7 overrides) unless you kept CF7 styling for the static form.
4. Keep all responsive media queries intact.

## Step 6: Clean the JavaScript

1. Copy `assets/js/script.js`.
2. Replace any jQuery usage if the original used `$` with jQuery dependency:
   - If simple DOM manipulation, convert to vanilla JS (`document.querySelector`, `addEventListener`).
   - If complex jQuery usage, include jQuery via CDN: `<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>`
3. Remove any WordPress-specific JS (Customizer preview bindings, wp.customize, etc.).

## Step 7: Fix All Paths

Search and replace all WordPress path functions:

| WordPress PHP | Static HTML |
|---|---|
| `<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/assets/images/photo.jpg` | `images/photo.jpg` |
| `<?php echo esc_url( home_url('/') ); ?>#section` | `#section` |
| `<?php echo esc_attr(...); ?>` | literal value |
| `<?php echo esc_html(...); ?>` | literal value |
| `<?php bloginfo('name'); ?>` | Site name string |
| `<?php echo date('Y'); ?>` | Hardcode year or use JS: `<script>document.write(new Date().getFullYear())</script>` |

## Step 8: Contact Form Replacement Options

| Service | Pros | Cons |
|---------|------|------|
| **FormSubmit.co** | No signup, free, honeypot spam filter | First submit requires email verification |
| **Formspree.io** | Free tier (50/mo), AJAX support, dashboard | Paid for higher volume |
| **Netlify Forms** | Built-in if hosting on Netlify | Netlify-only |
| **Basin** | Generous free tier, spam filtering | Third-party dependency |
| **Mailto link** | Zero dependencies | Poor UX, no structured data |

## Step 9: Deployment

Static sites can be deployed to:
- **one.com / Domeneshop** — SFTP upload to web root
- **Netlify / Vercel / Cloudflare Pages** — Git push or drag-and-drop
- **GitHub Pages** — Free for public repos
- **S3 + CloudFront** — Scalable, cheap

Example SFTP deployment script (PowerShell):

```powershell
# Use WinSCP, Posh-SSH, or sftp CLI
# Upload all files from local folder to remote web root
```

## Conversion Checklist

- [ ] All PHP removed — pure HTML/CSS/JS only
- [ ] All Customizer text replaced with hardcoded content
- [ ] All Customizer icon dropdown values replaced with hardcoded `<i>` class attributes
- [ ] All `lo_get_icon_choices()` and helper functions removed
- [ ] All conditional rendering wrappers (`if ! empty(trim(...))`) removed — static elements are present or deleted
- [ ] All CPT loops replaced with hardcoded HTML (including icons from meta boxes)
- [ ] CSS `auto-fit` grids reviewed — switch to fixed columns if item count is now static, or keep for responsive flexibility
- [ ] Contact form uses a third-party service (not CF7)
- [ ] All image paths converted to relative (`images/filename.jpg`)
- [ ] All anchor links work (`#section-id` matches `id="section-id"`)
- [ ] CSS theme header comment removed
- [ ] WordPress admin bar CSS removed
- [ ] `wp_head()` / `wp_footer()` replaced with explicit tags
- [ ] Page looks identical to the WordPress version
- [ ] Mobile responsive design still works
- [ ] All external resources (fonts, icons) loaded via CDN links in `<head>`
